{
  "uuid": "2d5c6e8b-6e32-4ff7-8a7e-f845b2173cb4",
  "name": "Selling film equipment on Facebook Marketplace",
  "summary": "**Conversation Overview**\n\nThe user wanted comprehensive help selling their film equipment on Facebook Marketplace, requesting assistance with all aspects including writing listings, pricing strategy, photo guidance, and logistics planning. They provided a detailed inventory of professional video and audio gear including Amaran LED lights (200x and 100x models), various softboxes, C-stands, sandbags, and audio equipment featuring an Audio-Technica AT875R shotgun microphone and Zoom H4n recorder. All items were described as used and working well, with the microphone being barely used.\n\nClaude provided a complete selling strategy with specific pricing recommendations based on retail values and used market rates, suggesting the AT875R microphone and Zoom H4n recorder represented the strongest value items in the collection. The total realistic selling range was estimated at $700-1,100. Claude recommended creating 2-3 category bundles rather than individual listings to reduce hassle, specifically suggesting a \"Complete Lighting Kit\" bundle and a \"Pro Audio Setup\" bundle alongside selective individual listings for buyers seeking specific items. The conversation concluded with Claude requesting photos of the equipment to finalize condition-based pricing and offering to create either customizable listing templates or ready-to-post Facebook Marketplace copy.",
